# .gitignore format & purpose
#
# - This file uses shell-style glob patterns. Common patterns:
#   *      matches any number of characters
#   ?      matches a single character
#   [a-z]  character class
#   /      path separator; patterns starting with '/' match from repo root
#   !      negate an ignore rule (un-ignore)
#
# - Keep secrets (like local .env) out of the repo by ignoring them.
# - This is a centralized repo-level ignore covering both frontend
#   and backend projects to avoid duplicated rules.
# - If you need to track a generated file, add an explicit "!path/to/file"
#
# Reference: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore

